- `git diff --check`

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Policy can now express direct-message scope, channel DM policy, open-group denial, group mention-gate, and channel-scoped ingress conformance requirements.

Real environment tested: WSL Ubuntu 24.04 checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-policy-ingress-channel`, rebased on updated #85817 and #85572 stack, using focused policy doctor and CLI tests.

Exact steps or command run after this patch: see Verification commands above.

Evidence after fix: focused tests cover failing ingress config, passing ingress config, disabled channel/account handling, inherited channel defaults, nested group mention overrides, Telegram root group inheritance for named accounts, and channel-scoped `channelIds` overlays.

Observed result after fix: the focused policy test suite passes with the new `channelIds` scoped ingress behavior and the docs/schema references point at `scopes.<scopeName>.ingress.channels.*`.

What was not tested: live channel runtime message delivery or enforcement; this PR intentionally adds Policy conformance/audit checks, not runtime enforcement.
